<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13443] Kafka broker exits when OAuth enabled and certain configuration not specified</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13443</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;sasl.oauthbearer.jwks.endpoint.retry.backoff.ms&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;sasl.oauthbearer.jwks.endpoint.retry.backoff.max.ms&lt;/tt&gt; configuration options were added to the &lt;tt&gt;SaslConfig&lt;/tt&gt; class but their default values were not added to &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConfig&lt;/tt&gt;. As a result, when the OAuth validation feature is enabled in the broker and those two configuration values aren&apos;t explicitly provided by the user, the broker exits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is to define them in the &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConfig&lt;/tt&gt; class.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
